modules.description: Provides functions for constructing and manipulating buffers to serialize data with minimal copying, supporting direct writes to file descriptors or custom output streams. Operates on byte sequences and custom data structures, enabling efficient serialization of complex types. Used to implement network protocols and data formats like JSON, allowing high-performance data transmission with low memory overhead.

Handles serialization of Faraday buffers with custom yield and writev callbacks, enabling controlled data emission in Lwt-based I/O pipelines. Operates on Faraday.t and bigstring I/O vectors for efficient memory management. Used to implement streaming protocols with precise control over data transmission flow.
